By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Lagos state, Kwara and Federal Capital Territory top the list of COVID-19 infections on Tuesday as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed 576 new cases of the dreaded virus in Nigeria. The health agency in its report released via its twitter handle noted that a total of 37,801 cases have been confirmed since the index case was reported in February 2010 while 15,677 patients have been treated and discharged within the period under review. The report further informed that  805 lives have been lost to the novel virus. The NCDC said that only 22 states out of the 36 states of the federation, including FCT recorded one or more infections on Tuesday and then details are as follows: Lagos-88;  Kwara-87;  FCT-82 ; Plateau-62;  Ondo-39 ; Enugu-28; Oyo-26; Taraba-24; Kaduna-20; Ebonyi-20; Edo-17;Cross River-16 ; Kano-14; Rivers-11; Ogun-10 ;Delta-9; Nasarawa-8; Osun-8 ; Katsina-3 ;Imo-2 ;Kebbi-1 and Borno-1. A breakdown of cases by states is shown below: 25 states in the country now have confirmed cases of the novel Coronavirus. According to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control as of Tuesday night, April 22, 782 confirmed COVID-19 cases were reported in the country. There have been 197 recoveries from the infection and 25 deaths so far. According… April 22, 2020 In "News" ABUJA (SundiataPost) - Nigeria is getting close to hitting the 30,000 mark in COVID-19 infections as 503 new cases were recorded on Tuesday night. According to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on its Twitter handle @NCDCgov on Thursday, with the new cases infections from the virus now total… July 8, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Seventy-six Nigerians died of COVID-19 in the last week, data from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) have shown. Also, 273 patients died of the disease in the country between May 20 and June 18, 2020. By the close of work on Friday, 12 June 2020, the… June 20, 2020 In "News"